appositive-pleonastic-pronoun: No NP is followed by a co-referential pronoun in the same grammatical role.
verb-stem: No bare verb stem is used with clear past-time reference; past forms are “was,” “did saw,” etc.
past-tense-swap: “cause I did saw a few” uses a simple past main verb after auxiliary did, where SAE requires the base form ('did see'), indicating nonstandard tense morphology in a simple past context.
zero-rel-pronoun: No subject relative clause modifies a noun without an overt relative pronoun; “over on the rooftop” is a PP, not a finite relative clause.
preterite-had: No 'had' + verb is used to express simple past.
bare-got: No 'got' is used to mean present possession.

sentence: And uh, I did saw someone climbing up    uh, uh I guess it was a sheet, to try to get off of  something, trying to get  uh, uh, up on the roof.
zero-poss: No possessive relationship is expressed without SAE marking; there is no noun–noun possessive or nonstandard possessive pronoun.
zero-copula: No required BE is missing; the copula is overt in 'I guess it was a sheet,' and other V‑ing forms are participial complements (e.g., 'saw someone climbing').
double-tense: No single verb shows duplicated past morphology within one word (e.g., no repeated -ed).
be-construction: No uninflected 'be' with habitual or generic meaning appears.
resultant-done: No aspectual 'done' precedes a verb phrase.
finna: No 'finna' or equivalent imminent future marker occurs.
come: No stance/evaluative 'come' is used; 'come' does not appear at all.
double-modal: No sequence of two modals (e.g., might could) occurs in a single clause.
multiple-neg: There are no negative elements in the clause (no 'not/ain’t/nobody/nothing').
neg-inversion: No clause-initial negative auxiliary precedes the subject.
n-inv-neg-concord: Neither the subject nor the finite verb shows overt negative marking.
zero-3sg-pres-s: No 3sg present-tense verb lacks -s; the finite verb is past ('did … saw') and other verbs are nonfinite.
is-was-gen: 'It was a sheet' has standard agreement; no generalized 'is/was' with nonmatching subjects.
zero-pl-s: No clearly plural noun lacks plural -s within its NP.
double-object: No personal dative sequence like 'I got me a NP' appears.
wh-qu1: There is no WH-question (no missing DO/copula in a WH-interrogative).
wh-qu2: No WH-clause is present, so no nonstandard WH word order occurs.
existential-it: 'It' in 'I guess it was a sheet' is referential, not existential.
demonstrative-them: The form 'them' does not occur before a noun as a determiner.
appositive-pleonastic-pronoun: No NP is followed by a co-referential pronoun in the same grammatical role.
verb-stem: There is no bare finite verb with clear past reference; past is marked via 'did' and (nonstandardly) 'saw'.
past-tense-swap: No use of a past participle as simple past or irregular/regularized past swap; 'did saw' is nonstandard but not of the defined swap types.
zero-rel-pronoun: No finite subject relative clause modifies a noun; modifiers are nonfinite (e.g., 'someone climbing').
preterite-had: No 'had' + verb is used to express simple past.
bare-got: No 'got' is used to mean present possession; only 'get' appears in nonfinite forms.
